main event: A fast-moving, brilliant unidentified object was observed by four crew members of an aircraft at an altitude of 11,000 feet heading 090 degrees.
interesting points: The object appeared to be a disc traveling at high speed, faster than an F-104 jet.
The object made a 180-degree turn towards the observer's aircraft.
The object emitted a brilliant light that turned on and off repeatedly over the 2-3 minute sighting.
The object was observed from approximately 090 degrees to 220 degrees magnetic, 40 to 20 degrees above the horizon.
The total sighting duration was 2-3 minutes.
witnesses: four crew members of an aircraft
